          "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
          "position": [
            -1088,
            -992
          ],
          "parameters": {
            "color": "#FEC942",
            "width": 372,
            "height": 812,
            "content": "## AI Resume Job Title Extractor\n\nAnalyses a PDF resume using Google Gemini and extracts the candidate's current job title. Designed to run as a sub-workflow called by the Job Search automation.\n\n### How it works\n1. Triggered by a parent workflow via the Execute Workflow trigger\n2. Reads the candidate's PDF resume from the local filesystem\n3. Extracts raw text from the PDF\n4. Sends the text to Gemini with a prompt to identify the current job title\n5. Returns the extracted job title and Gemini response parts to the calling workflow\n\n### Setup\n1. **Resume File**: Update the file path in the 'Read/Write Files from Disk' node to point to your resume PDF\n2. **Google Gemini**: Connect your Google Gemini (PaLM) API credentials in the 'Message a model' node\n3. **Model**: Uses Gemma-4-31B by default — swap in any Gemini model you prefer\n\n### Customisation\n- Adjust the prompt in 'Message a model' to extract different info (skills, years of experience, etc.)\n- Edit 'Return' to pass additional fields back to the parent workflow"
          },
          "typeVersion": 1
        },
        {
          "id": "sticky-section-1",
